Package ch.bfh.ti.sed.patmon1.server.controller.fault

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    FaultBean
    FaultBean which is used by JAX-WS to send custom Exceptions.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    DeviceAlreadyAssignedException
    Used if a device is tried to be assigned to an observation period which is already assigned.
    DeviceNotAssignedException
    Used if a device should be returned, which is not assigned.
    EntityAlreadyExistsException
    Used if the client tries to persist an entity of which there is already an entity in the database with the given primary key.
    EntityNotFoundException
    Used if a server business object is not found in the database.
    IllegalStateException
    Used if a request is invalid because the server is in a specific state which does not allow the request to be made at the moment.
    InvalidSessionException
    Used if there is no valid session for a request to the SessionControllerProxy.
    NotLoggedInException
    Used if a login fails.
